Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces (no need to peel). Mince @chives{1/4%oz}.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use all the Fry Seasoning.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While carrots roast, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid; drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} using a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed.

Stir in half the chives. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat.

> 4 SERVINGS: Mash potatoes with 2 packets sour cream and 2 TBSP butter.

== Buffalo-Spiced Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt and pepper.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #shallow microwave-safe dish{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Brush @sour cream{1%tbsp} onto tops of chicken in a thin layer. Working one piece at a time, dip brushed sides of chicken into panko mixture, pressing to adhere.

Place coated sides up on a second, lightly oiled baking sheet.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter in panko mixture and 2 packets sour cream on chicken.

Roast chicken on middle rack until cooked through, ~{15-18%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @blue cheese dressing{1.5%oz}, remaining sour cream, and remaining chives.

== To Serve ==

Divide carrots, potatoes, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with blue cheese sauce and @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired. Serve with any remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.